description:
Available at: https://openstudionetwork.com/keezer - These lessons contain useful tools and exercises to set your hands free of the traditional "roles" assigned to left and right, as well as introducing dynamics and arranging concepts. (Note: Geoffrey recommends his video Comping Independence Exercise (link) as a prerequisite to this pack.)

Includes:
Playing the melody and comping with the same hand
The "middle hand" - dividing melodies between the hands
"3-D" dynamics - a visual approach to dynamics
"Inside Movers" - an introduction to countermelodies
Level: Intermediate
fulltitle: Geoffrey Keezer - SOLO PIANO: Freeing Up Traditional Hand Roles
